2,north,"**Analyzing the Sokoban Puzzle**

Okay, so I'm a priest, currently at coordinates (39, 15), and the goal is to get boulders onto fountains. Looking at the map, I see a boulder immediately to my east, and another one further east. The problem? I can't push two boulders at once, and if I try to move east I'll be stymied. Let's see... the fountain is actually south of me at (39, 16).

I need to figure out how to maneuver a boulder onto the fountain. Pushing the boulder at (40,15) south is blocked. Hmmm. I also consider moving North, East, East, East, South, West to push a boulder. But that's a lot of steps. 

I see the map around me and consider that the boulder at (36, 15) is also a candidate. I need to get east of that to push it. Going north from (39,15) to (39,14) is feasible, but then heading west is blocked by walls at columns 36 and 37.

But wait, there's a clear path on y=13! I can go north to (39, 13), and then move west. Then I can get to the boulder! This is the plan: I'll go north to (39, 14), then north again to (39, 13), then west all the way to (35, 13). Then south to (35, 14), then south to (35, 15). At that point, I'll be east of the boulder at (36, 15), ready to push it east, which will also push the stairs!

